{"cursor":"3124","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Anil Kumar Bhattacharya' (also spelled 'Anil Kumar Bhattacharyya', Bangla: à¦à¦¨à¦¿à¦²\nà¦à§à¦®à¦¾à¦° à¦­à¦à§à¦à¦¾à¦à¦¾à¦°à§à¦¯) was an Indian statistician who worked at the Indian\nStatistical Institute founded by P C Mahalanobis in the 1930s and early 40s. He\nmade fundamental contributions to multivariate statistics, particularly for his\nmeasure of similarity between two multinomial distributions, known as the\nBhattacharya coefficient, based on which he defined a metric, the Bhattacharya\ndistance. This measure is widely used in comparing statistical samples in\nbiology, physics, computer science, etc.\n\nDistance between statistical distributions had been addressed in 1936 by\nBhattacharyya's mentor, Mahalanobis, who proposed the D 2 metric, now\nknown as Mahalanobis distance. Subsequently Bhattacharya defined a cosine metric\nfor distance between distributions, in a Calcutta Mathematical Society paper in\n1943, {{cite journal |first=A. |last=Bhattacharyya |title=On a measure of\ndivergence between two statistical populations defined by their probability\ndistributions |journal=Bulletin of the Calcutta Mathematical Society |volume=35\n|pages=99â109 |year=1943 |mr=0010358 }}  expanding on some of the results\nin another paper in Sankhya in 1947.\n\nSometime in the 1940s, Bhattacharya left ISI. C R Rao, Prasantha\nChandra Mahalanobis (1893-1972), Biographical Memoirs of Fellows of the Royal\nSociety, v.19 (Dec 1973), pp.455-492 He served as a faculty of Department\nof Statistics, Presidency College, Calcutta from 1941 to 1974. {{cite book\n| title = Essays on probability and statistics : Festschrift in honour of\n| Professor Anil Kumar Bhattacharyya author = S. P. Mukherjee, Arijit Chaudhuri,\n| Sujit K. Basu editor = A. M. Gun on behalf of the Organizing Committee, Golden\n| Jubilee Celebrations publisher = Department of Statistics, Presidency College\n| year = 1994 | isbn = | page = }} He also served as a distinguished\n| Professor as Ramakrishna Mission Residential College, Narendrapur, where a\n| Memorial Scholarship is awarded in his name.\n","linknr":104,"url":"A._Bhattacharya","recorded":1364182481,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Anil_Kumar_Bhattacharya&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Anil_Kumar_Bhattacharya&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Anil_Kumar_Bhattacharya","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.wikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=A._Bhattacharya&redirect=no","#mw-head","#p-search","/wiki/Bangla","/wiki/Statistician","/wiki/Indian_Statistical_Institute","/wiki/P_C_Mahalanobis","/wiki/Multivariate_statistics","/wiki/Bhattacharya_coefficient","/wiki/Metric_(mathematics)","/wiki/Bhattacharya_distance","/wiki/Mahalanobis_distance","/wiki/Cosine_similarity","/wiki/Calcutta_Mathematical_Society","#cite_note-1","/wiki/Sankhya_(journal)","#cite_note-crrao-2","/wiki/Presidency_University,_Kolkata","#cite_note-Festschrift-3","/wiki/Ramakrishna_Mission_Residential_College,_Narendrapur","#cite_note-4","/w/index.php?title=Anil_Kumar_Bhattacharya&action=edit&section=1","#cite_ref-1","/wiki/Calcutta_Mathematical_Society","/wiki/Mathematical_Reviews","http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=0010358","#cite_ref-crrao_2-0","/wiki/C_R_Rao